{"id": "duc04-testb-23:9#28", "contents": "Brazil has been caught up in the financial turmoil that began more than a year ago in Southeast Asia. As wary investors have fled its financial markets, Brazil's foreign reserves have fallen below dlrs 50 billion from dlrs 70 billion at the end of July. The outcome of the gubernatorial elections will likely determine how successful Cardoso is in getting Congress to approve his economic program, which is aimed at trimming the budget deficit. New income, fuel and bank transaction taxes are expected to be proposed. Kugelmas said opponents of the president stand a good chance of winning in four large states _ Sao Paulo, Minas Gerais, Rio de Janeiro and Rio Grande do Sul."}
